---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Shipping — DOKU">
  <div class="narrow">
    <div class="page-head">
      <div class="eyebrow">Where it goes, and how</div>
      <h1 class="serif">Shipping</h1>
      <p>Every piece ships once, to one person. Here's what that actually looks like.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Where we ship</h2>
      <p>Currently, DOKU ships within India only. If that changes, this page will say so before checkout does.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>How each piece is packed</h2>
      <p>Nothing here comes off a warehouse shelf. Once your order is confirmed, the object is inspected and packed individually before it leaves us — a one-of-one gets one-person handling, not an automated line.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Tracking your order</h2>
      <p>Your order moves through four stages — Reserved, Confirmed, Shipped, Delivered — visible any time on your <a href="/account">account</a> page. Once it ships, we add a tracking note there too.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Delivery time</h2>
      <p>Because each object is handled individually rather than mass-fulfilled, timing varies by piece and destination. We'd rather tell you honestly at each stage than promise a number we can't guarantee.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>Shipping cost</h2>
      <p>The price shown at checkout is the full price — we don't add shipping charges on top of it.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>If something goes wrong in transit</h2>
      <p>If an object is damaged or lost before it reaches you, see <a href="/refund-policy">Refunds &amp; Cancellations</a> — this is one of the cases we do refund in full.</p>
    </div>

    <p class="fine-print">Questions about a specific order — <a href="/inquire">Inquire</a>, with your order code.</p>

    <div class="legal-updated">Last updated 17 July 2026</div>
  </div>
</Base>
